            <div>
                <head>“I TOO”</head>
                
                <lg><l>I, too, sing America.</l></lg>
                
                <lg><l>I am the darker brother.</l>
                <l>They send me to eat in the kitchen</l>
                <l>When company comes.</l>
                <l>But I laugh,</l>
                <l>And eat well,</l>
                <l>And grow strong.</l></lg>
                
                <lg><l>To-morrow</l>
                <l>I’ll sit at the table</l>
                <l>When company comes</l>
                <l>Nobody ’ll dare</l>
                <l>Say to me,</l>
                <l>“Eat in the kitchen”</l>
                <l>Then.</l></lg>
                
                <lg><l>Besides, they’ll see how beautiful I am</l>
                <l>And be ashamed,—</l></lg>
                
                <lg><l>I, too, am America.</l></lg>
                
                <byline>Langston Hughes</byline>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
